<HEADLINE> South Africa's Producer Inflation at Two-Year High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 31 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's Production
Price Index (PPI) showed an annual rate of increase of five
percent in February, the highest since September 1997, when it was
6.1 percent, Statistics South Africa announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This rate is 0.6 percentage points higher than the
corresponding rate of 4.4 percent in January.
</P>
<P>
The annual increase of five percent in the PPI is mainly due to
a 3.9- percentage-point increase in the price index for locally
produced commodities. The annual increase in imported commodities
is 1.1 percentage points.
</P>
<P>
The annual rate of increase in the PPI for locally produced
commodities is 4.8 percent in February, compared with the
corresponding annual rate of four percent in January. 
</P>
</TEXT>
