<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cholera Kills 153 Zimbabweans Since January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 31 (Xinhua) -- A total of 153 Zimbabweans have
been killed by cholera since its outbreak this January, the
Zimbabwean Ministry of Health and Child Welfare announced here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said in a statement that a total of 1,623 cases
were reported during the period despite efforts to curb the spread
of the disease.
</P>
<P>
"The current spread of cholera has been fuelled by people
travelling to and from affected areas without due regard to
adherence to adequate hygienic practices," said the ministry.
</P>
<P>
It urged the private sector to compliment its efforts by
giving support for the anti-cholera campaigns to bring the
epidemic under control.
</P>
<P>
Cholera is contracted through eating food or drinking water
contaminated by the cholera germ. The patients lose body fluids
and, if not promptly replaced, they would become weak and die.
</P>
</TEXT>
