<HEADLINE> 36 Illegal Immigrants Netted in Tanzanian Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Tanzanian authorities
have seized 36 illegal immigrants in capital Dar es Salaam this
year, the Immigration Department said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A public relations officer at the department, Herbert Chilambo,
told reporters that the illegal immigrants came from Kenya, India,
Somalia, Burundi, the Democratic Republic of Congo, Yemen, France,
the Sudan, Pakistan, and the Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Chilambo said some of the netted have been expelled from
Tanzania while others are either being prosecuted or handled at
the Immigration Department.
</P>
<P>
He called on people to support the government in seizing
illegal immigrants by providing information to relevant
authorities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
