<HEADLINE> Clinton Approves 50 Mln Dlr Refugee Aid for Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 31 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton
Wednesday approved 50 million U.S. dollars of aid for refugees
from the Yugoslav province of Kosovo, White House Press Secretary
Joe Lockhart said.
</P>
<P>
"The president today is authorizing an additional 50 million
U.S. dollars to address the urgent humanitarian needs of refugees
who fled Kosovo," Lockhart said.
</P>
<P>
He said the money would be drawn from an emergency contingency
fund and the Department of Defense. Half will be sent to the U.N.
High Commission on Refugees and half will pay for food and
shelter.
</P>
<P>
Additionally, the U.S. Agency for International Development
sent a disaster relief team to Albania to assess the growing
humanitarian crisis, Lockhart said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
