<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Invests $90 mln in Angola's Diamond </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Russia and the former Soviet Union
have invested about 90 million U.S. dollars in developing diamond
in Angola since 1980, a senior Russian official said here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Vladmir Raevski, Russian Ambassador to Angola, said after his
meeting with Angolan Geology and Mineral Minister Manuel Bunjo,
that the money has been invested on the Catoca Project in
northeastern Angola's Lunda-Norte Province, a diamond-rich
province bordering the Democratic Republic of Congo.
</P>
<P>
The Catoca Project is a joint venture between Angola's National
Diamond Company and Russia's Arma Company and Brizalia's Odebrecht
Company.
</P>
<P>
The Russian ambassador said that Angola has obtained Russia's
high technology in diamond development through the joint
development.
</P>
<P>
 Bunjo said at the same time that Russia and Angola have
cooperated for 20 years in diamond industry, saying that he has
discussed various issues concerning further corporation between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan minister said that to further develop the
corporation between the two countries in diamond industry will be
top on the agenda of the coming Angolan-Russian Mixed Committee
this year.
</P>
<P>
Angola is an important diamond producer in Africa, with the
government- controled mines turning out about two million karat of
diamond last year. Russia, South Africa and Belgium are the major
foreign investors in Angola' s diamond industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
