<HEADLINE> Vice Premier Speaks on Infant Education, Youngsters' Health </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Vice Premier Li Lanqing at a
seminar today urged governments at all levels, related
organizations, schools and parents to pay attention to the
education, nutrition and health of infants and youngsters.
</P>
<P>
Li, who is also member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party
of China, said that a life-long system of education should be
established to replace the current system of receiving education
mainly at schools.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the importance of physical education, urging
schools and indeed the whole society to provide more space and
facilities for youngsters so as they can take regular exercises
more conveniently.
</P>
<P>
According to the vice premier, Chinese students, and especially
infants, should have their nutritional intake improved with more
milk and soybean products. "I hope that every student will be able
to have one cup of dairy or soybean milk everyday," he said.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the role played by families in the education
of infants and the improvement of youngsters' nutrition and health.
</P>
