<HEADLINE> Chilean Writers Denounce NATO Bombing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Chilean Writers Association
(CWA) on Wednesday announced their most vigorous condemnation of
the bombing and intervention by the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO) in Yugoslavian territory.
</P>
<P>
At the same time they expressed their protest against the
interference of a political and military alliance in a non allied
nation, such as the Federal Republic of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Such determination was made public on Wednesday in a statement
by the writers group signed by the president, Edmundo Herrera, and
the general secretary, Virginia Verdal and corresponds to the
agreement adopted last Monday.
</P>
<P>
The statement expresses that "the Chilean writers are against
the war, for the defense of world peace. We do not want NATO to
begin world war three, which may also signify the end of the
planet. We demand the end of the bombings and the start of
diplomatic talks".
</P>
<P>
In addition, the writers are against the attitude of the large
powers "which are establishing themselves as the police force of
humanity. We demand that the United Nations (UN) comply with their
role as defenders of the populations".
</P>
<P>
Finally, the society demand that the mediums of national
communication are opened to the whole information and truth about
the real events, "because the Chileans are overwhelmed by the
dis-information".
</P>
<P>
"It is not correct that only people with access to cable
television are well informed". 
</P>
</TEXT>
