<HEADLINE> NATO Missiles Striking Bulgaria Intolerable: Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Bulgarian Interior Minister Bogomil
Bonev on Thursday condemned the presence of NATO missiles striking
Bulgarian territory. He called it intolerable, the Bulgarian News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The missile falling in Bulgaria Wednesday was launched by the
NATO air force from Yugoslav air space near the Bulgarian border.
It could have done great harm to civilians had it fallen within
residential areas, Bonev said.
</P>
<P>
Wreckage from another missile was found on Bulgarian territory
last Friday. The two missiles are of the same type, he said.
</P>
<P>
Bulgarian President Peter Stoyanov also expressed his concern
over missile incidents during a meeting with a high NATO official
here Thursday. 
</P>
