<HEADLINE> NATO to Stop Strike Only Serb Stops First: Solana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Chief of the North Atlantic
Treaty Organization (NATO) Javier Solana said here Thursday that
NATO will stop air attacks against Yugoslavia only when President
Slobodan Milosevic stops fighting.
</P>
<P>
"NATO will stop only he stops," Solana told reporters at the
Brussels-based NATO headquarters when he and NATO Supreme
Commander Wesley Clark were briefing assessment on NATO attacks in
