basketball Association (CBA) All-Sstars game will be held in
Shanghai on May 8 featuring the South and North teams for the
contest, the CBA announced on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese basketball All-Stars, beginning from the 1995-96
season, will change its competing way of last season from a
Chinese-star team vs. a Foreign-star into the South vs. North
including two foreign-stars eath team.
</P>
<P>
The Forign-star ralied to edge the Chinese-star 83-80 at the
last All-Stars game in Shenyang, Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
The South side brackets players from the Bayi Rockets,
Guangdong Tigers, Shanghai Sharks, Zhejiang Cyclone, Jiangsu
Dragons and Sichuan Pandas.
</P>
<P>
While the other six sides - the Liaoning Hunters, Shandong
Flaming Bulls, Beijing Ducks, Jilin Northeast Tigers, Beijing
Aoshen and Jinan Army - will compose of the North side.
</P>
<P>
The All-Stars will be selected on a countrywide fan's poll.
