<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Talks With Kuchma </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 1 (Xinhua)-- Russian President Boris Yeltsin and
his visiting Ukrainian counterpart Leonid Kuchma exchanged the
ratified version of the friendship and cooperation treaty between
the two countries on Thursday which put the 10-year-long treaty
into effect.
</P>
<P>
The friendship and cooperation treaty between Russia and
Ukraine was signed by Yeltsin and Kuchma in May, 1997. Due to
disputes on issues regarding the Crimea and the Black Sea Fleet,
the treaty was not ratified by the parliaments of the two
countries until March 24, 1999.
</P>
<P>
While meeting with Kuchma at the Kremlin, Yeltsin stressed the
need for a strategic partnership between the two countries. He
said Russia and Ukraine should take careful and responsible action
to safeguard the stability of Europe and the world.
</P>
<P>
NATO's air strikes against Yugoslavia triggered a new crisis
throughout Europe and makes cooperation between the two countries
even more urgent, he added. Kuchma expressed the same view in
saying a friendship and cooperation treaty is indispensable to
bilateral relations as well as the security of Europe.
</P>
<P>
Kuchma was in Moscow for the summit meeting of the Commonwealth
of Independent States. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
