<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 34 Die From Diseases in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-four persons have died
from common cold, cough and fever in the past month in two
villages of Sindhupalchok district, central Nepal, Radio Nepal
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
It said the diseases have spread to two neighboring villages.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, an outbreak of viral influenza has claimed about 700
lives in five districts of mid-western Nepal in less than one
month, The Kathmandu Post daily reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Himalayan kingdom is prone to various diseases as access to
sanitation in the country is only 18 percent compared with South
Asia's average of 36 percent, according to the Asian Development
Bank. 
</P>
