<HEADLINE> Construction of the Oriental Plaza Progresses Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the Oriental Plaza,
jointly invested by Beijing and a Hong Kong business tycoon with
1.96 billion U.S. dollars, is progressing smoothly and the
superstructure is expected to be completed by October 1, China's
National Day, according to Beijing Party chief Jia Qinglin.
</P>
<P>
While meeting with Hong Kong businessman Li Ka-Shing, the
plaza's primary investor, Jia said today that the Oriental Plaza
has been listed as one of the city's key projects, and its
construction has drawn the full attention of both the Central
Government and the Beijing Municipal Government.
</P>
<P>
The Oriental Plaza will be a multipurpose complex including
hotels, apartment and office buildings and shops, covering a total
area of 110,000 square meters or equivalent to 12 football courts,
and with a total floor space of 900,000 square meters, or five
times that of the Great Hall of the People, where China's top
legislature sits. 
</P>
