<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Talks on Northern Ireland's
deadlocked peace process will be adjourned until April 13, British
Prime Minister Tony Blair announced on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He said at a press conference in Belfast that a basis for
agreement to set up a Northern Ireland executive has been agreed.
</P>
<P>
Blair made the announcement after nearly two days of talks at
Hillsborough Castle south of Belfast.
</P>
<P>
