<HEADLINE> Kunming Ready for '99 World Horticulture Exposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The city of Kunming in southwest
China's Yunnan Province is now well-prepared to host the '99 World
Horticulture Exposition, the largest international event ever held
in China.
</P>
<P>
All construction projects will be completed at least 15 days
before the exposition opens on May 1, and infrastructure
facilities have been greatly improved, Governor Li Jiating of
Yunnan Province said today.
</P>
<P>
This capital city of Yunnan has invested more than one billion
yuan (about 120 million U.S. dollars) to build the main exhibition
halls and create gardens displaying the art of horticulture and
plants from some 90 countries and regions around the world.
</P>
<P>
Roads, telecommunication facilities and power-supply networks
have been greatly upgraded in Kunming, and the number of standard
hotel beds has been increased from 20,000 to more than 50,000.
</P>
<P>
Factories around Dianchi Lake, a famous tourist resort near
Kunming, today were ordered to reduce industrial discharges into
the lake and meet the pollution standards set by pollution-control
departments.
</P>
<P>
The six-month-long exposition is expected to receive about 10
million visitors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
