<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 13 NATO Members Participate in Bombardment of Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The ongoing open-ended NATO bombing
of Yugoslavia has involved troops and military facilities from 13-
member countries of the U.S.-led Western military alliance, the
Russian military said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Information collected by Russia shows that 300 planes, some 40
warships and more than 12,000 ground troops from the 13 NATO
countries are taking part in the military action in Yugoslavia,
the General Staff of Russia's Armed Forces said in a report.
</P>
<P>
NATO warplanes have made more than 750 sorties over Yugoslavia
and over 350 cruise missiles have been launched from land or
airplanes at targets in the Balkan country since NATO's massive
bombardment began on March 24, the report said.
</P>
<P>
NATO has also used two U.S. B-2 stealth bombers in the air
strikes. The bombers flew directly to Yugoslavia from their base
in the United States. Boeing E-3 early warning planes are also
playing a role in the action.
</P>
<P>
During the air campaign, the report said, NATO experimented
with a series of new and highly precise weapons, including cruise
missiles and guided aerial bombs, which can reduce losses as
warplanes are able to hit targets without entering the range of
the Yugoslav Air Defense Force. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
