<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Urges Speedier Afforestation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao
today urged related departments to hasten tree-planting and
greening efforts to significantly improve the country's ecological
environment in ten to fifteen years.
</P>
<P>
At a plenary session of the National Greening Committee today,
Wen, also head of the Committee, said that although China has been
launching large-scale afforestation drives for two decades, the
nation's forest cover is still relatively low, and many places are
still suffering from soil erosion and ecological degeneration.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that past experience shows that in order to
achieve optimum results in these efforts, all of society should be
fully mobilized, and relevant laws should be strictly observed.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier also emphasized the importance of public
awareness and technology in the afforestation drive.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the State Council issued an action plan for China's
ecological improvement which called for a combination of economic
development and ecological improvement.
</P>
<P>
According to the vice premier, the state will greatly increase
investment in greening projects this year and in the future.
</P>
<P>
At today's meeting, 530 people who have made remarkable
contributions to afforestation and greening were rewarded with
National Greening Medals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
