<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Suspended From Volleyball Internationals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The International Volleyball
Federation (FIVB) has decided to suspend Bulgaria from all
participation of international events until a satisfactory ending
of the conflict between the national federation recognised by the
FIVB and a new federation which contests its legitimacy.
</P>
<P>
The FIVB announced the decision throuth a new release on
Thursday in Lausanne, Switzerland, but did not indicated the
beginning day of the suspension in its statement.
</P>
<P>
The release said the two conflicting federations have reached
an agreement on March 23 in Sofia to create an intermediate
organism before the end of the month of April, in charge of
preparing an extraordinary general assembly to form an unique
Bulgarian Volleyball Federation recognised by the FIVB.
</P>
<P>
The FIVB Board of Administration will meet for a definite
decision on the issue on May 5-7 in Lausanne. 
</P>
</TEXT>
