<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, April 1 (Xinhua) -- A visiting delegation from Home
Depot, the world's largest household appliance retailer, expressed
willingness here today to set up enterprises in China.
</P>
<P>
An executive of the company, which is seeking collaborative
opportunities in north China's largest port city of Tianjin, said
that his company also has confidence that they will be able to
find the commodities they need in China.
</P>
<P>
Home Depot imported some 400 million U.S. dollars worth of
commodities from China last year.
</P>
<P>
A senior Chinese official said that an increasing number of
international chain stores are exploring various products made in
China and the country's enormous market.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China is now capable of producing more than 100,
000 kinds of consumer goods, thanks to 20 years of reform and
opening-up which have greatly improved the country's manufacturing
capabilities.
</P>
<P>
The official added that the Chinese government has required its
foreign trade enterprises to have close links with the purchasing
system of international chain stores.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese government encourages the domestic
retail industry to compete with overseas chain stores, and also
encourages the internationalization of the Chinese market. 
</P>
