<HEADLINE> China Collects Huge Relief Funds Through Lottery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- China has raised 1.5 billion yuan
(about 180 million U.S. dollars) in special relief fund for
victims of last summer's floods by issuing lottery tickets
nationwide since last October, announced Doji Cering, Minister of
Civil Affairs, at a press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
All the funds collected through these special lotteries were
turned over to the State Council immediately, and will be used to
reconstruct flood-stricken areas and aid the floods victims, the
minister said.
</P>
<P>
He said the successful issuing of special-purpose lotteries
demonstrates the Chinese traditional virtue of helping each other,
and the good credit and reputation of lotteries issued by civil
affairs departments.
</P>
<P>
State Councilor Ismail Amat was present at today's press
conference and said he hopes this successful lottery issue will
help to establish a relief-fund raising mechanism under the market
economy . 
</P>
</TEXT>
