<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Yemeni Vice-Presidents Hold Talks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- China strongly urges NATO to
immediately stop its military operation against Yugoslavia in
order to bring the Kosovo issue back to the negotiating table for
a political solution.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-President Hu Jintao made the remarks during talks
with his Yemeni counterpart Abdo Rabo Mansour Hadi here this
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Hu said the recent escalation of NATO military operations has
aroused strong response worldwide. "We feel shocked and uneasy,"
he told Hadi.
</P>
<P>
Hu reiterated that the Chinese government advocates that the
Kosovo issue should be resolved through dialogue on the basis of
respecting Yugoslavia's sovereignty and territorial integrity and
ensuring the lawful rights of all ethnic groups in the Kosovo
region.
</P>
<P>
He restated that China consistently advocates properly
resolving territorial or border disputes between countries
through dialogue and consultations, opposes the use of force or
the threat of the use of force, and supports all efforts
conductive to peaceful solutions.
</P>
<P>
On bilateral relations, Hu said that China cherishes its
traditional friendship with Yemen and is willing to make common
efforts with Yemen for the development of a long, stable, mutually
beneficial, and cooperative friendly relationship well into the 21
st century.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the profound traditional friendship between China and
Yemen, bilateral relations have witnessed sustained and healthy
development since the formation of diplomatic ties over 40 years
ago, Hu said, adding that cooperation between the two countries in
many fields is well-grounded, fruitful, and promising for the
future.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president also expressed his appreciation for Yemen's
adherence to a "One China" policy and its support of China on the
human rights issue.
</P>
<P>
Hu highly praised the achievements made by the Yemeni people
under the leadership of President Ali Abdullah Saleh in
accomplishing national unification, maintaining state stability
and developing national economy.
</P>
<P>
He also appreciated the peace, neutral, and good-neighbor
foreign policy adopted by the Yemeni government, as well as its
contribution to maintaining regional peace and stability.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
