<HEADLINE> Russia Sends Warship to Mediterranean for Security Reasons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 1 (Xinhua)-- A Russian reconnaissance warship
will be sent to the Mediterranean on Friday to ensure the
country's security because NATO is expected to launch its phase-3
aggression against Yugoslavia, said Russian Foreign Minister Igor
Ivanov Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ivanov said he had informed U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright of the decision to send the warship there.
</P>
<P>
The warship will collect information to ensure that Russia can
know the all developments at any time and get itself prepared.
</P>
<P>
Russian Defense Minister Igor Sergeyev announced Wednesday that
Russia would soon send seven warships to the region around the
Yugoslavia conflict and the first reconnaissance ship is to leave
its Black Sea base on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Turkey on Wednesday also approved a Russian request for the
passage of its warships through the Bosporus straight.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Ivanov said that Russia would soon put forward new
proposals on how to solve the Yugoslavia crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
