<HEADLINE> HK Chief Executive to Visit Canada, U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) will visit
Canada and the United States from May 9 to 14, the SAR government
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
The visit aims at strengthening Hong Kong's ties with the two
countries and to update political and business leaders there on
developments in Hong Kong, the announcement said.
</P>
<P>
As the Hong Kong SAR is due to enter the third year of its
establishment, Tung will reassure overseas audiences of Hong
Kong's continued role as a regional business and financial center,
and as the pre-eminent gateway to the Chinese mainland and the
east Asian region, the government said.
</P>
<P>
Tung will exchange views with U.S. and Canadian political and
business leaders on financial, business and trade issues. He will
also use the opportunity to brief them on the latest developments
in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The government said Tung will emphasize Hong Kong's advantages
as a business and service center, and the importance the SAR
attaches to the development of information technology and other
high value-added industries.
</P>
<P>
The chief executive will visit Toronto, Ottawa, San Francisco,
and the Silicon Valley.
</P>
<P>
Secretary for Trade and Industry Chau Tak Hay and Information
Coordinator Stephen Lam will be accompanying Mr. and Mrs. Tung on
the visit.  
</P>
</TEXT>
