<HEADLINE> Ethnic Culture Museum Opens inn SW China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, April 1 (Xinhua) -- China's first museum of the Sui
ethnic group has opened in Guizhou Province, southwest China.
</P>
<P>
The Sui, who mainly inhabit southern and northwestern parts of
Guizhou, have a long history.
</P>
<P>
The museum has been built in the Sandu Sui Autonomous
Prefecture and contains more than 1,000 exhibits with historical
documents and cultural relics showing the group's history, social
structure, folk customs, calendric system, language, clothing, and
architecture.
</P>
<P>
The museum also has exhibits on cultural exchanges with other
Chinese ethnic groups.  
</P>
</TEXT>
