<HEADLINE> NATO Campaign "Long and Difficult": British Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 1 (Xinhua) - British Defense Secretary George
Robertson said on Thursday that the NATO campaign in Yugoslavia
would be "long and difficult".
</P>
<P>
Speaking to Britain's Sky television, Robertson said the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization "has the determination and stomach"
to keep on the bombing as long as possible.
</P>
<P>
The air strike against Yugoslavia stretched into its ninth day
on Thursday. NATO said on Wednesday that the bombing would be
intensified and expanded as a number of new targets had been
chosen.
</P>
<P>
Robertson had been in sombre mood late on Wednesday when he was
reporting to British House of Commons on the conflict. There are
more and more critics now in the parliament who said the air
strikes have sparked more violence in Kosovo and the bombing
should be stopped as soon as possible. 
</P>
</TEXT>
