<HEADLINE> Share Prices Shoot Up on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 1 (Xinhua)-- Share prices shot up on Singapore
Stock Market Thursday spurred by the expectation that Deutsche
Bank may launch another issue of covered warrants on the local
shares of major banks.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said Deutsche Bank is planning a new issue following
good demand for its issue last month.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index ran up 26.88 points to
1,545.19 points in brisk dealings
</P>
<P>
The total volume surged up to 434.63 million units valued at
618.74 million Singapore dollars (358.64 million U.S. dollars).
Gainers outstripped losers by 254 to 42 with 131 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Econ w00 topped the actives chart of the day with a turnover of
26.25 million shares. It was followed by MHE w99 which had 22.29
million shares done. Wing T was next with a volume of 20.29
counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
YHS was the top mover of the day soaring up 160 cents to close
at 4.78 Singapore dollars. GE Life and SPH 100 ran up 80 cents and
finished at 11.40 and 20.00 Singapore dollars respectively. SPH
climbed up 70 cents to end at 19.80 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Venture w99 led descent of the day shedding 30
cents to 6.70 Singapore dollars. DBS F sank 10 cents to finish at
13.00 Singapore dollars. Datacrft retreated eight cents to end at
2.26 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers noted that today's rally came ahead of a long weekend
as the market is shut on Friday for Good Friday and reopens on
Monday. 
</P>
