<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Stronger </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar hopped more
than half a U.S. cent higher ahead of the Easter long weekend,
largely inspired by technical factors and late squaring of
positions.
</P>
<P>
At the close the local currency was buying 63.58 U.S. cents, up
from Wednesday night's close of 62.98.
</P>
<P>
