<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen Stresses Governing of Macao According to Law (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Qian Qichen, vice-premier of the
State Council, stressed here today that the long-term stability
and sound development of Macao can be achieved only through the
rule of law.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a forum marking the sixth anniversary of the
promulgation of the Basic Law of the Macao Special Administrative
Region (MSAR), Qian pointed out that the Basic Law is the
essential guideline for handling all matters related to the
transition and noted it will serve as a basis for drawing up each
principle and policy for the future MSAR.
</P>
<P>
Adopted on March 31, 1993 at the first session of the Eighth
National People's Congress, the Basic Law was drawn up after four
years' extensive study and after soliciting the opinions of people
from all walks of life in mainland areas of China and in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Every year since relevant central departments have marked the
anniversary of the promulgation of the Basic Law. This year's
forum is the last before the return of Macao to the motherland on
December 20, 1999.
</P>
<P>
Qian noted that the Basic Law is the constitutional law of the
future MSAR and is essential for the future of the region.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he said, a comprehensive study and understanding of
the Law is necessary, especially as it will go into effect in
eight months.
</P>
<P>
The Law must be publicized among Macao residents and mainland
people, he noted, adding that this must be in line with the
preparations for the MSAR.
</P>
</TEXT>
