<HEADLINE> Tokyo's Nikkei Closes Above 16,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
TOKYO, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices soared in Tokyo
Thursday, the first day of Japan's new fiscal year, with the key
Nikkei index closing above 16,000.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock Exchange soared 490.97 points, or 3.10
percent, from Wednesday's close to end at 16,327.56.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors continued their strong appetite for Tokyo
stocks while investors with oversold positions rushed to buy back
after seeing significant gains in share prices, traders said.
</P>
<P>
Arbitrage-linked buying, stirred by a rise in index futures
prices, was another factor lifting share prices, they said.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index (TOPIX), covering
all First Section issues, advanced 33.22 points or 2.62 percent to
1,300.44.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section expanded to 725.98 million
shares from Wednesday's 480.43 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Mitsubishi Electric was the day's most heavily traded issue.
</P>
<P>
Share prices moved up in all business sectors except the air
transportation industry and nonbanking money lenders, with the
companies that had announced sweeping restructuring programs most
favored by the investors, traders said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
