<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey Allows Russian Warships to Pass Through </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Turkish government has given the
green light to a Russian naval squadron to pass through its
straits into the Mediterranean Sea in early April.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the Foreign Ministry Wednesday night said
the Russian embassy in Ankara had presented two requests for the
passage of eight Russian warships through its straits.
</P>
<P>
The fleet will include a missile carrier, anti-submarine
frigates and other escort vessels from the Black Sea Fleet.
</P>
<P>
The warships will pass through the Canakkale and Bosphorus
Straits linking the Black Sea to the Mediterranean between April 3
and 8.
</P>
<P>
The passage of foregin warships through the Turkish straits is
overseen by the 1936 Treaty of Montreux.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the Black Sea littoral states can sail
their ships through the straits if they inform Turkish
authorities of their intentions at least eight days in advance.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the Russian warships would be carrying out
"reconnaissance tasks" in the war zone "because of the ongoing
situation in Yugoslavia." 
</P>
</TEXT>
