<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Urgent: Myanmar Calls on NATO, Yugoslavia to Peacefully Solve the Conflict </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar government has called on
all parties concerned to peacefully solve the conflict between the
North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) and the Yugoslavia, said
a press release of the Myanmar Ministry of Foreign Affairs issued
here Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The press release said that Myanmar has been following with
great concern the current situation in Yugoslavia which has
resulted in loss of many innocent men, women and children.
</P>
<P>
Recent events have also shown that the conflict has the
potential to spread to other countries in the region as well, it
stated.
</P>
<P>
"The Myanmar government therefore calls on all parties
concerned to try and resolve the issue through peaceful means,
respect for the principles enshrined in the Charter of the United
Nations and respect for the independence, sovereignty and
territorial integrity of Federal Republic of Yugoslavia," it
added.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for the Myanmar government to issue a
press release on the NATO-Yugoslavia conflicts since NATO started
airstrikes against Yugoslavia on March 24 without the
authorization of the U.N. Security Council. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
