<HEADLINE> China Makes Continuous Diplomatic Efforts to Solve Kosovo Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- China has been making efforts to
find solution to the Kosovo crisis, said Foreign Ministry
spokesman Sun Yuxi here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Sun told a routine press conference that Chinese President
Jiang Zemin, during his just-concluded European visit, made a
short speech on the Kosovo crisis in Italy to express his concern
and worry about the military operation, and urged an immediate
stop of such operation at the night when NATO launched air strikes
against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Foreign Ministry at the night also issued a
statement announcing the stance of the Chinese government on the
issue, he said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president later made speeches on different
occasions to reiterate China's principled stand, he said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Jiang on March 29 sent an oral message to Yugoslav
President Slobodan Milosevic and a letter in reply to U.S.
President Bill Clinton, Sun said.
</P>
<P>
In the messages the Chinese president again urged an immediate
halt to military interference in order to bring the issue back to
the track of political solution.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan also made open remarks on
the Kosovo issue during his just-ended European tour, Sun said.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, China appreciated Russia's active
efforts on the Kosovo issue.  
</P>
</TEXT>
