<BODY>
<HEADLINE> '99 China International Youth Volunteer Work Camp </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIANDU (Zhejiang), April 1 (Xinhua) -- The `99 China
International Youth Volunteer Work Camp opened in Xiandu in east
China's Zhejiang Province today.
</P>
<P>
More than 20 volunteers from China, Japan, the Netherlands,
Australia, and Canada will do various types of voluntary service
for local people during the 10-day camp to improve the environment
by planting trees, repairing roads, and providing other social
services. They will also be able to visit scenic spots and have
exchanges with local students.
</P>
<P>
Hu Qiaoliang, the deputy magistrate of the county where the
camp in being held, said at the opening ceremony that volunteers
will sow the seeds of friendship with their voluntary service and
it will give them a chance to promote mutual understanding.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the voluntary service will also
promote an awareness of the need for environmental protection and
help develop local tourism.
</P>
<P>
Most of the volunteers are in China for the first time, and
some have come for study. Twenty-year-old Marcela Kraemerova from
the Czech Republic, the youngest volunteer, says that she hopes to
do something useful for environmental protection and to learn more
about Chinese culture and history.
</P>
<P>
The camp was organized by the All-China Youth Federation (ACYF)
It has held 3 previous camps for desert afforestation, protecting
cultural relics, and assisting the disabled. 
</P>
</TEXT>
