<HEADLINE> China Expecting Growth In Garment Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- China's garment industry is
expecting to maintain growth in 1999 and its total retail sales
are projected at 3.1 trillion yuan, up 7 percent from 1998.
</P>
<P>
Garment sales this year are expected to account for 13.2
percent of total retail sales, an increase of 5.6 percent,
according to today's China Reform News.
</P>
<P>
The paper says that per capita spending by urbanites will be
about 4,670 yuan this year, up 5 percent, with spending on
clothing averaging 540 yuan, up 3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Per capita spending of rural people is expected to be some 1,
180 yuan, up 2 percent, with clothing accounting for 115 yuan, up
4 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
