<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Hails Martyred "Hero" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 1 (Xinhua) -- A young service man who died
fighting last summer's devastating floods on the Yangtze has been
commended as a model soldier by Chinese President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Li Xiangqun, a member of the Guangzhou Area Command, was
credited with saving the lives of five people, including elderly
people, children and a fellow soldier, according to a decree
released today.
</P>
<P>
But Li himself died, aged only 20, in the course of his duty,
and Jiang, who is also chairman of the Central Military Commission,
described him as a hero because of his brave actions.
</P>
<P>
According to reports, despite being severely injured he
struggled to find survivors along the Yangtze dike, battling the
raging floodwaters. He collapsed four times before he was sent to
hospital.
</P>
<P>
However, when he regained consciousness, he removed the drip-
feed from his arm and courageously returned to the dikes, there
sacrificing his youthful life on behalf of others.
</P>
<P>
Jiang called on all service men and women to learn from Li's
devotion to duty and urged them to follow his example.  
</P>
</TEXT>
