<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya Bans Night Fishing in Lake Victoria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan government has
prohibited night fishing in Lake Victoria, in a bid to stamp out
fishing with poison under cover of darkness.
</P>
<P>
The ban, which took effect immediately, was announced
Wednesday by Kenyan Natural Resources Minister Francis Lotodo, the
Daily Nation newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
 Lotoda sounded out a warning that any fisherman caught using
poisonous chemicals to harvest fish would be dealt with
ruthlessly.
</P>
<P>
The minister also said the government would provide motor-boats
to the relevant departments to enable them to patrol the lake
more effectively.
</P>
<P>
He appealed to the residents living around the lake, the
world's second largest fresh water lake, to cooperate with police
and provincial administration officers in cracking down on fishing
with poison.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan government issued a health alert Tuesday over fish
poisoning in Lake Victoria, which borders Kenya, Tanzania and
Uganda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
