<HEADLINE> NZ Changing Focus from Building Ships to Conversions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand shipbuilding
industry is changing its focus from building new ships to luxury
refits and conversions.
</P>
<P>
A Wellington-based newspaper Thursday quoted Northland Port
Chief Executive Vern Dark as saying there is a definite trend
toward luxury conversions and the shipbuilding industry in
Whangarei, the most important shipbuilding base in New Zealand,
is well placed to capitalize on that.
</P>
<P>
"Conversion work is definitely a trend at the moment," Dark
said, adding "We'll be seeing more and more older vessels
transformed into luxury passenger yachts."
</P>
<P>
Whangarei's shipbuilding industry has been hard hit in recent
years due to the economic conditions in the world.
</P>
<P>
However, an emphasis on diversification and specialization to
counter the changing economic environment is beginning to pay off,
Dark said.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand has the skills to take on specialist projects at
significantly lower cost than shipyards in the United States or
Europe, the Dominion quoted NZ Marine Industrial Project
Management principal Warwick Stevenson as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
