<HEADLINE> Three US Soldiers Captured in Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Yugoslav state television on
Thursday showed footage of three captured U.S. soldiers who
admitted they were "captured on Yugoslav territory on March 31."
</P>
<P>
The television identified the three were "officers Andrew
Ramirez and Stone James, and soldier Steven Gonzalez."
</P>
<P>
 Three U.S. Army soldiers on a reconnaissance mission on the
Macedonia-Yugoslavia border were missing Wednesday night after
being fired upon, the U.S. Pentagon officials said.
</P>
<P>
 The three men, wearing US army uniforms, were shown sitting
and answering questions with no facial expression. Their voices
could not be heard. 
