<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Snow, Rain Ease Drought In Western China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, April 1 (Xinhua) -- The snow and rain that hit the
northern part of northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region March 29-31 have helped ease the drought problems of the
warm temperatures of last month.
</P>
<P>
By 8:00 a.m. on March 31, the city of Shihezi had had 17.5 mm
of rain and Urumqi, the regional capital, had had 13.7 mm of snow,
according to the Xinjiang Meteorology Center.
</P>
<P>
The snow and rain are good for the winter wheat and spring
planting, but the low temperatures brought in by the cold front
have made it difficult for livestock in the northern part of the
region to move to other grassy areas.
</P>
<P>
Meteorologists predict that the temperatures will not change
significantly in the near future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
