<HEADLINE> Ancient Silk Road Expecting More Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, April 1 (Xinhua) -- Five provinces and autonomous
regions in northwest China are joining together to promote visitor
attractions along the ancient Silk Road, in an effort to boost the
local tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
The Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region, Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region and the provinces of Shaanxi, Gansu and Qinghai are to
highlight the grottoes, scenic sites, cultural relics, Buddhist
culture and folklore on the Silk Road this year.
</P>
<P>
Local tourist authorities said that they have prepared five
excellent programs for overseas and domestic visitors which link
up with local tourist spots and cities.
</P>
<P>
Northwest China began to develop a tourism cooperative network
a decade ago. More than 200 million overseas and domestic tourists
have so far visited the area.  
</P>
