<HEADLINE> Republic of Korea Promotes Investment in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, April 1 (Xinhua) -- A move by the government of the
Republic of Korea (ROK) to encourage foreign investments by small-
to medium-sized enterprises is expected to sharply increase
related investments in China.
</P>
<P>
A leading ROK official in charge of related businesses recently
visited northeast China's Liaoning province and noted increased
investments in China will help his nation overcome current
economic difficulties.
</P>
<P>
"China offers vast market potential which facilitates expanded
production and will create good opportunities for ROK businesses
suffering from the depressed domestic economy and overproduction,
according to the official from the Presidential Commission on
Small and Medium Business.
</P>
<P>
ROK-based Trigem Computer Inc. will launch its largest PC
manufacturing base in China this October. The new venture will
have an annual production capacity of 1.2 million PCs.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to attract an additional 30-odd small-
to medium-sized ROK enterprise producing compatible products and
will in turn facilitate the development of a large computer
industrial park in Shenyang, the provincial capital.
</P>
<P>
The official added that small- to medium-sized enterprises
represent a major driving force in the ROK economy, with the vast
majority of over 120,000 related enterprises planning to expanding
overseas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
