<HEADLINE> International Drug Traffickers Captured in Panama </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Panamanian police cracked an
international drug trafficking gang and seized seven kilograms of
cocaine on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"After a long surveillance in Panama City, our units performed
an operation in the airport of Tocumen, and finally captured nine
members of the gang, of whom five are Colombians," said the head
of the Anti-Drug Unit of the Judicial Technical Police (JTP),
Ruben Reina.
</P>
<P>
The gang was going to send the cocaine to Spain, he added.
</P>
<P>
Drug smugglers often employ "mules" to traffic the drugs, most
of whom are young women, who carry the cocaine strategically
hidden in small bags in purses and in shoes with double soles.
</P>
<P>
"This criminal organization previously introduced the cargo of
drugs into Panamanian territory, to be sent later to the markets
of high consumption in the U.S. and Spain," said Reina. 
</P>
