<HEADLINE> Shanghai Volkswagen Develops New Santana Sedan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Volkswagen
Automobile Corp., a Sino-German joint venture, has developed a new
generation Santana sedan which is scheduled to roll off the
assembly line later this year.
</P>
<P>
The third generation Santana, based on German-built Passat B5
sedans, is adapted to China's road conditions and is expected to
fulfill local market demand.
</P>
<P>
The environmentally friendly model features 1.8 liter engines,
air bags and safety belts.
</P>
<P>
