<HEADLINE> Ronaldo May Need Surgery for Tendinitis in Knee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Soccer star Ronaldo may need surgery
to eradicate the tendinitis in his right knee, said his
physiotherapist in Milan on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"It's a possibility, but surgery would be the very last
solution," Nilton Petrone said. "We will do everything possible to
avoid it and recent improvements let us believe that Ronaldo's
knee can be cured."
</P>
<P>
Petrone said the injury has been troubling the Brazilian star
since the World Cup, and Ronaldo, who plays for Internazionale of
Milan, will have to work harder than teammates to recover his form.
</P>
<P>
"He still feels some pain in his right knee, while the left
knee is OK now," Petrone said at Inter's training camp.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian physiotherapist, a longtime friend of Ronaldo,
has been added as a member of the Milan's club's medical staff to
personally tend to the Brazilian striker, a two-time FIFA World
Player of the Year.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo, who has been repeatedly sidelined by knee problems
this season, has played only portions of matches in the European
Champions League and Italian Serie A.
</P>
<P>
"He still is at 50 percent, but he's improving," Petrone said.
</P>
