<HEADLINE> More Kosovo Refugees Pour Into Albania, Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 31 (Xinhua) -- More refugees from Yugoslavia's
Kosovo province continued to pour into Albania and Macedonia on
Wednesday, with their number in Albania alone exceeding 100,000,
the Albanian news agency ATA reported.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Macedonian Prime Minister Ljubco Georgievski said
the situation in Macedonia was also very serious after more than
35,000 refugees entered the country.
</P>
