<HEADLINE> Russia Condemns US-led NATO Plan to Separate Kosovo from Yugoslavia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 31 (Xinhua) -- Russian Foreign Minister Igor
Ivanov Wednesday condemned the US-led NATO for planning to
separate Kosovo from Yugoslavia and stressed that Russia would
take more measures to stop it.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference here, Ivanov said Russia has got
accurate information that NATO is actively planning to separate
Kosovo from Yugoslavia, and to send in ground forces to reinforce
the Kosovo Liberation Army (KLA).
</P>
<P>
Refuting Western media reports that the Russian peace mission
to Belgrade failed, he said the mission led by Premier Yevgeny
Primakov had received a clear message from Yugoslavia for a
political solution to the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
But NATO rejected the peaceful message, showing it has no
intention for such a solution, he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Defense Minister Igor Sergeyev said on the same
occasion that in view of the current situation in Yugoslavia, his
ministry plans to propose to the state leadership to "take more
resolute measures."
</P>
<P>
He said the Russian military is now moving to raise its combat
readiness to safeguard Russian and its allies' security.
</P>
<P>
NATO's aggression against Yugoslavia has proved a conclusion by
his ministry long ago that NATO is a military alliance used by the
United States to implement its power policies, he added.
</P>
<P>
He warned what is happening in Yugoslavia now could repeat in
any other independent and sovereign country in the future.
</P>
</TEXT>
