<HEADLINE> Mexican Volcano Spews Steam, Ash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, March 31 (Xinhua) -- The Popocatepetl volcano, 60
kilometers south of Mexico City, has increased its activity over
the last 24 hours, blasting steam and gas into the air, Mexico's
National Center for the Prevention of Disasters (NCPD) said on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The NCPD said that 15 major blasts had occurred since Tuesday
afternoon, one of which lasted 10 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Steam and gases rose 200 meters above the summit of the volcano,
where windspeeds are between 28 and 55 kilometers per hour.
</P>
<P>
The NCPD warned local population to stay a minimum of seven
kilometers away from the volcano, adding that it was uncertain
whether a full-scale eruption would occur. 
</P>
