<HEADLINE> France Struggles 2-0 to Beat Armenia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 31 (Xinhua) -- World Cup champion France struggled
to beat lowly Armenia 2-0 in a Group 4 European championship
qualifier in Saint-Denis, France, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Sylvain Wiltord shot his first international goal in the third
minute and Nicolas Anelka weaved through two challenges before
letting the ball run to the Bordeaux striker, who stroked the ball
past goalkeeper Roman Berezovski from 15 meters.
</P>
<P>
France had to wait until first-half stoppage time for its
second goal, headed in by Christophe Dugarry after Laurent Blanc
had nodded a left wing corner onto the crossbar.
</P>
<P>
In the last 15 minutes, Berezovski did well to save long-range
efforts from Robert Pires and Alain Boghossian.
</P>
<P>
The rusty France, which drew 0-0 with Ukraine here last
Saturday and could only beat tiny Andorra 2-0 in November, lacked
width and was normally too labored in its approach play to create
chances against a packed Armenian defense.
</P>
<P>
Armenia couldn't match the physical presence of Didier
Deschamps and Patrick Vieira in midfield, but was always quick to
pack its defense to keep the score respectable. 
</P>
