</P>
<P>
HELSINKI -- Finnish Prime Minister Pavvo Lipponen and his
government resigned Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
President Martti Ahtisaari has accepted the resignation.
Lipponen and his government will act as caretaker government until
the new government is formed, possibly in mid-April. (Finland-
Resignation)
</P>
<P>
