PARIS -- Six more French warplanes will join the NATO Armada
engaged in the bombing operations against Yugoslavia, said French
Defense Minister Alain Richard on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Agence France-Presse quoted Richard as saying the unspecified
planes would come into action within 48 hours. (NATO-Kosovo-
Warplanes)
</P>
<P>
